  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nFutures are mixed with small caps (IWM +0.57%) leading while tech and large caps struggle. VIX spike to 29.33 signals elevated anxiety as Iran war headlines dominate the tape. Energy crisis narrative is building momentum with materials catching a bid.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Retail Sales Data (12:30 ET)</strong> - Full suite of retail numbers could move markets significantly given consumer spending concerns</li>\n<li><strong>ADP Employment (12:15 ET)</strong> - Weekly employment data adds to labor market picture ahead of Friday's jobs report</li>\n<li><strong>UnitedHealth Earnings Beat</strong> - Healthcare giant topped estimates and raised outlook, but sector still down -0.93% pre-market</li>\n<li><strong>Iran War Energy Impact</strong> - IEA calling this \"biggest energy crisis in history\" - watch crude and energy names</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nMaterials (XLB +0.67%) and financials (XLF +0.38%) are leading as war premium drives commodities higher. Healthcare getting hit despite UNH beat - defensive rotation failing. Small caps outperforming suggests risk-on sentiment beneath the surface volatility.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Iran war escalation creating supply chain disruptions across multiple sectors - from energy to industrial commodities. Hormuz Strait concerns are real.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>VIX above 29 with energy crisis rhetoric building. If retail sales disappoint, consumer spending narrative collapses just as geopolitical risks peak.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Small caps leading suggests rotation into domestically-focused names. Materials and industrials catching bids on infrastructure